what is best dvd r or dvd r hi oskape the dvd r and dvd r are competing formats much like the old vhs and beta formats in video tapes today most drives are hybrid and handle both formats they are usually labeled dvd r the market for recordable dvd technology shows little sign of settling down in favor of either the plus or dash formats which is mostly the result of the increasing numbers of dual format devices that can record to both formats it has become very difficult to find new devices that can only record to one of the formats however because the dvd r format has been in use since it has had a five year lead on dvd r as such older or cheaper dvd players up to vintage are more likely to favor the dvd r standard exclusively and when creating dvds for distribution where the playing unit is unknown or older the dvd r format would normally be preferable my personal experience has led me towards using the r it is slightly better at error handling so more tolerant of dirty or damaged media and also more tolerant to the subtle differences between players as far as the best brand is concerned we did a lot of comparison testing and found verbatim the very best sony was a decent middle of the road and memorex was the absolute far and away worst norm DVD Videocassette recorder Laserdisc VHS Compact disc Betamax Sony Floppy disk High-definition television 8 mm video format MP3 Camcorder Videotape Compact audio cassette Gramophone record DualDisc Redundant array of independent disks TiVo CD-ROM Computer and video games Betacam Video CD PlayStation 3 Blu-ray Disc Universal Serial Bus Television Format war Gmail Video 2000 Phonograph High fidelity Video codec Digital photography Karaoke Delta Goodrem Console wars Microsoft S-VHS ZX Spectrum Digital video recorder Audiophile Integrated Services Digital Broadcasting S__CAM JVC Handheld game console Windows Vista PlayStation 2 Game controller DVD-R DVD-RAM Warez Embedded system Macrovision Enterprise content management Podcasting